    <note>Lin(1) G [20191] His son, Xun(3) [20192] (q.v.), has the same phonetic element in his mingzi as one of Guojun's [20188] (q.v.) grandsons, which also fits with a chronology which would make G a son of Guojun. Lin(1) Yizhi [11073] was junior to Xun(3), which probably means that Xun(3) was an older lineage cousin. G and Xun(3) came from a lineage, whose first famous member held the title, Guozi siye, which was a title held by Lin(1) Guangchao [10612], documented lineage nephew of Guojun. I am, therefore, identifying G as a son of Guojun and Yizhi as a lineage nephew of Guangchao. Lin Yizhi, WJ, 4.91-10b (wife, born Zheng, who died in 1181 at age 86--thirty nine years after the death of G).</note>
